{
  "stem": "27507.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Lots of houses were burning.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were so frightened by that bombardment as well that we thought of leaving Rowne all together.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But a few days later, two or three days later, the Red Army came.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that was part of the [INAUDIBLE] of Poland between the Germans and the Russians that was a result, a direct result of the Molotov-Ribbentrop pact signed in Moscow in August 1939.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that whole part of Poland where we were, the whole eastern part of Poland from the frontier with Soviet Union to the River Bug, which was now to the west of us, was occupied by the Red Army.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When the Red Army came, we saw them in the street, coming in the street.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that was one of those memories that I still carry with me until today.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were not-- they were-- because it was an amazing view.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They didn't come in one in a column, but they came rather in groups, in bands.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They had-- they looked rather disorganized.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They had still their old type of pointed helmets, pointed heads like, which I later found out were used by them during the revolution.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they all together looked like some kind of partisan bands then a proper army.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And of course, we were glad in one way that the Russians came, because that meant that there were no more bombardments.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "On the other hand, a day or two later, after the Red Army came, some military with-- with blue and red, blue and red insignia on-- on their hats, with a I think blue ring around their hat, came to my-- to the villa of my-- of my father's cousin and asked for him to come to the military command.",
      "word_count": 60
    }
  ],
